                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/279: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-07T14:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 7, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. My telegram No. 20, March 6, 6 p.m. Honduran Minister for Foreign Affairs now
                    tells me that Honduran Government now agrees with Nicaragua, Salvador, and
                    Guatemala to hold Conference on March 15 as originally planned, and that
                    Honduran delegates will be appointed tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Central American missions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
